                <div class="about">
                    <div class="about-head">
                        <h2>About This Blog Website</h2>
                        <p>This is a simple blog application built to practice and demonstrate my full-stack web development skills using Node.js, Express, PostgreSQL, and EJS. Users can register, log in, create, edit, and delete their blog posts.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="about-grid">
                        <div class="about-tech">
                            <h3>Technologies Used</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Node.js + Express.js for backend</li>
                                <li>PostgreSQL for database</li>
                                <li>EJS for templating</li>
                                <li>Bootstrap and custom CSS for UI</li>
                                <li>bcrypt for password hashing</li>
                                <li>express-session for user sessions</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="about-features">
                            <h3>Key Features</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>User registration and login system</li>
                                <li>Create, edit, and delete blog posts</li>
                                <li>Responsive design using Bootstrap</li>
                                <li>Session management with express-session</li>
                                <li>Secure password handling with bcrypt</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="about-project">
                            <h3>Why I Built This</h3>
                            <p>I created this project as part of my learning journey in web development. It helped me understand server-side rendering, RESTful routing, user authentication, and session management. This blog serves as a portfolio project and a base for future improvements.</p>
